    "Beginning in 1928, Kennedy published an ultimately 7-volume series of photographic portfolios, <em>Studies in the History and Criticism of Sculpture</em>, assisted in some cases by the American School and initially co-published with the Carnegie Corporation of New York.": [],
    "An eighth volume was abandoned for publication but the photos circulated.": [],
    "He was promoted to (full) Professor of art at Smith in 1930.": [],
    "He reliquished his graduate studies directorship in 1932, teaching as a visiting professor of fine arts, New York University the same year.": [
